quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,"The All-Merciful"
  55,2,"taught the Recital{1}",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is <i>Qur’an</i> which literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  55,3,"created man,"
  55,4,"and taught him clear expression."
  55,5,"The sun and the moon move according to plan,"
  55,6,"and the plants{1}and the trees prostrate themselves.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is <i>najm</i> which also means ‘star’; notice the suitability of the term which connects what is before it with what is after it.
  55,7,"And the sky—He raised it and set up the balance,"
  55,8,"so do<sup>pl </sup>not exceed in the balance,"
  55,9,"but maintain the weights justly and do not fall short in the balance."
  55,10,"And the earth—He set it up for living creatures;"
